webpackJsonp([7656638037465],{515:function(t,a){t.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>A bounty table shows how much your program is willing to pay for various bugs you receive. They help set expectations for hackers and gives your bug bounty team a guideline to ensure fair and consistent reward amounts. The bounties in the table are categorized based on the severity of the issue identified. </p>\n<p>To set up and publish your bounty table on your security page:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to your programâ€™s <strong>Settings > Rewards > Bounties</strong>. </li>\n<li><i>(Optional)</i> Edit the column names of the bounty table that best fit the reward structure of your program under the <strong>Bounty Table</strong> section. </li>\n<li>Select the asset you want the bounty structure to apply to. If you want it to apply to all assets, the default is already set to <strong>All assets</strong>.</li>\n<li>Input your bounty amounts under each column. </li>\n<li><i>(Optional)</i> To add another row to your bounty table, click <strong>+ add another bounty table row</strong>. </li>\n<li><i>(Optional)</i> Add a description about how severity is determined or you can also add examples of what types of bugs fall into which category in the <strong>Optional description</strong> field.</li>\n<li>Click <b>Create bounty table</b>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-b3eca.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 67.59581881533101%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="bounty-tables-1"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-e7ffa.png"\n        srcset="/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-49813.png 125w,\n/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-dc8a5.png 250w,\n/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-e7ffa.png 500w,\n/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-dda24.png 750w,\n/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-c5f18.png 1000w,\n/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-22484.png 1500w,\n/static/bounty-tables-1-37d456f06a6187bab39e24e8766a49d6-b3eca.png 1722w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Your security page will now have a Rewards section that showcases your bounty table.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-a5787.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 28.095238095238095%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="bounty-tables-2"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-e7ffa.png"\n        srcset="/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-49813.png 125w,\n/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-dc8a5.png 250w,\n/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-e7ffa.png 500w,\n/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-dda24.png 750w,\n/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-c5f18.png 1000w,\n/static/bounty-tables-2-1fdb4d899b0169beb0796782ad304db6-a5787.png 1260w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>To remove the bounty table from your security page, select <strong>Remove bounty table</strong> under <strong>Settings > Rewards > Bounties</strong>.</p>\n<p>Setting up a bounty table will help provide more granular data and analytics for your program, which will in turn, help your program become more successful. </p>',frontmatter:{path:"/programs/bounty-tables.html",id:"programs/bounty-tables",title:"Bounty Tables",description:null}}},pathContext:{}}}});
